                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "deathNote": true,
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>If Jervis is destroyed, he rejuvenates back in the underground chambers below Chopper's Isle and seeks out the carrier of the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Clockwork Songbird]{Clockwork Songbird's} head as long as they remain within 5 miles of Sandpoint. If the architect of his whole doom, the Red Bishop, is slain, Stoot can move on to the afterlife.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>When a ghost is destroyed, it re-forms after [[/br 2d4 #days]]{2d4 days} within the location it's bound to, fully healed. A ghost can be permanently destroyed only if someone determines the reason for its existence and sets right whatever prevents the spirit from resting.</p>"
                },
