                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Jervis Stoot raises a hand high, and a murder of ghostly crows manifests in a vortex above his hand. He then lowers his hand to point in a direction, and the murder of ghostly crows swarms out in a @Template[cone|distance:20]. All creatures caught in the area must attempt a @Check[reflex|dc:30] save. Jervis can't use Ghostly Murder again for [[/br 1d4 #Recharge Ghostly Murder]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes @Damage[6d6[slashing]] damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[10d6[slashing],2d6[bleed]]{10d6 slashing damage and 2d6 bleed} damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[15d6[slashing],5d6[bleed]]{15d6 slashing damage, 5d6 bleed} damage, and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Blinded]. The blindness persists until it's healed via an effect like restore senses.</p>"
                },
